{
  "texts": [
    "Brdesee et al (2022) proposed a sequential DL model based on LSTM to predict the at risk of failing students, to ensure that students graduate on time, and to assess the student's number on campus in a particular year and their projection for succeeding years.",
    "The dataset used was from the LMS platform of a Saudi university and contained demographic, educational, learning, and academic features.",
    "The imbalance in academic award-gap performances and timely/late graduates was eliminated using the synthetic minority over-sampling technique for class balancing.",
    "The results showed that the LSTM model was more effective than the other ML models for the early identification of at risk students, achieving an accuracy of 85%.",
    "Authors Year Dataset Dataset Size Features Features No Tech Evaluation Measurements Contributions Limitations Aljohani et al (2019) 2019 MOOC (OULAD) 32,593 students Learning Behavior/Activity features 20 LSTM Accuracy: 95.23% Precision: 93.46% Recall: 75.79% The study has transformed the learning behavior/activity features into a sequential format in order to improve the level of students who are at-risk of fail Dataset used does not have sufficient course-level records Liu et al (2020) 2020 Math homework and classwork of students provided by ASSISTments 338,001 logs consisting of 4,216 students and 24,896 exercises Learning Behavior/Activity features 24 LSTM AUC: 98% Accuracy: 97% RMSE: 0.26 MAE: 0.20 The proposed model (MFA-DKT) fused multiple features, including student exercise features and behavior/activity features, to trace student knowledge states."
  ]
}